p with.\n\n01:16:47.500 --> 01:16:52.500\nAnd it's like, get the, get, get seriously, get out, get out of here.\n\n01:16:52.500 --> 01:16:54.500\nThe arrogance is astounding.\n\n01:16:54.500 --> 01:16:55.500\nOut of here.\n\n01:16:55.500 --> 01:17:03.500\nEspecially when even for your time, it was already, it was already a, a, a confident bet.\n\n01:17:03.500 --> 01:17:11.500\nIt wasn't, it wasn't like all the rage was guys in ridiculous tin man costumes, like\n\n01:17:11.500 --> 01:17:12.500\nthat looked like tanks.\n\n01:17:12.500 --> 01:17:15.500\nIt wasn't like, oh, you just rode that, those coattails.\n\n01:17:15.500 --> 01:17:20.500\nIt was like, it would already been established that if you just trust this like singular\n\n01:17:20.500 --> 01:17:24.500\ntone and let it be its own thing and then for them to go like, yeah, but everything's black\n\n01:17:24.500 --> 01:17:25.500\nand rubber now.\n\n01:17:25.500 --> 01:17:29.500\nIt's hot, but I don't want to bag on that stuff and shake my cane at it.\n\n01:17:29.500 --> 01:17:34.500\nBut they're, it's important to note, so you got Robocop, you got Robocop two, you got\n\n01:17:34.500 --> 01:17:39.500\nRobocop three, where I think there's like ninjas in that one and a jet pack.\n\n01:17:39.500 --> 01:17:40.500\nThere's been a cartoon.\n\n01:17:40.500 --> 01:17:42.500\nThere's been a, all kinds of stuff.\n\n01:17:42.500 --> 01:17:43.500\nComic books.\n\n01:17:43.500 --> 01:17:45.500\nAnd then the, there's the reboot, which I didn't watch.\n\n01:17:45.500 --> 01:17:46.500\nSo I don't know what it was.\n\n01:17:46.500 --> 01:17:47.500\nIt was a Canadian TV series.\n\n01:17:47.500 --> 01:17:48.500\nCanonically.\n\n01:17:48.500 --> 01:17:50.500\nPrime directive.\n\n01:17:50.500 --> 01:17:54.500\nNow they're, I don't know what stage they're at.\n\n01:17:54.500 --> 01:18:02.000\nThey can fill us in on the details, but they're, they, they're going to do a sequel to the\n\n01:18:02.000 --> 01:18:04.500\noriginal that ignores all of this other stuff.\n\n01:18:04.500 --> 01:18:07.500\nIs that, that's what I, well, we'll see what's going to happen.\n\n01:18:07.500 --> 01:18:08.500\nAnd we'll see.\n\n01:18:08.500 --> 01:18:12.500\nAnd, but I have to say that MGM has been very, very nice to me since the reboot.\n\n01:18:12.500 --> 01:18:18.500\nI, when I got credited because of the WGA, I had to go in and meet with them.\n\n01:18:18.500 --> 01:18:21.500\nAnd I met with the, the president of MGM.\n\n01:18:21.500 --> 01:18:26.500\nAnd you'll see online, as I was confused, it's like, like Ed's got a credit on the 2014\n\n01:18:26.500 --> 01:18:31.500\nRobocop reboot, which micro broke a little part of my heart for a second.\n\n01:18:31.500 --> 01:18:33.500\nWell, it was, I had nothing to do with it.\n\n01:18:33.500 --> 01:18:34.500\nRight.\n\n01:18:34.500 --> 01:18:36.500\nIt was sort of nice to get the residuals.\n\n01:18:36.500 --> 01:18:42.500\nAnd it's because just to clarify, it's, it's because the writers in, in basing it on your\n\n01:18:42.500 --> 01:18:48.500\nkind of your, your, your characters and your story, they evoked enough of it, that arbitration.\n\n01:18:48.500 --> 01:18:54.500\nThey took so many pieces of it and used it that in the arbitration process, they, they\n\n01:18:54.500 --> 01:18:56.500\nassigned us a fair amount of credit for it.\n\n01:18:56.500 --> 01:19:01.500\nNow I feel like that's got to feel good because that's not even like the, the, like it's,\n\n01:19:01.500 --> 01:19:05.500\nit's a, it's a, it's a maybe like a 15 year old boy fantasy to be like, yeah.\n\n01:19:05.500 --> 01:19:08.500\nAnd then, and then they did it without me and it sucked.\n\n01:19:08.500 --> 01:19:16.500\nAnd it's like, it's, but like that's a, that's a proper like mentor wizard fantasy of like,\n\n01:19:16.500 --> 01:19:22.500\nit's been 30 years and these kids are trying your craft and like the blood magic gets out\n\n01:19:22.500 --> 01:19:28.500\nof control and you're just like, yeah, you're, you're, you're sitting there and you're lazy\n\n01:19:28.500 --> 01:19:30.500\nboy and you're like, oh, I felt a tingle.\n\n01:19:30.500 --> 01:19:34.500\nSomeone's trying to do what I did again.\n\n01:19:34.500 --> 01:19:37.500\nThey always, they always think they, they, they're always sure that what they're doing\n\n01:19:37.500 --> 01:19:38.500\nis the right thing.\n\n01:19:38.500 --> 01:19:44.500\nDo you feel like maybe you can, or can't talk about what stage this new possible straight\n\n01:19:44.500 --> 01:19:48.500\nsequel thing is, but do you feel confident if you went back and tried to do the sequel\n\n01:19:48.500 --> 01:19:53.500\nthat you have, like, that you, like, you know where you're going with that and you could\n\n01:19:53.500 --> 01:19:54.500\npull it off?\n\n01:19:54.500 --> 01:19:56.500\nWe've had, we've had a bunch of conversation about this.\n\n01:19:56.500 --> 01:20:00.500\nI was going to, what happened, which was interesting was I went in when they were,\n\n01:20:00.500 --> 01:20:03.500\nwhen I, when I met them, they'd all just finished this movie, hadn't come out yet.\n\n01:20:03.500 --> 01:20:07.500\nAnd I had a kind of, it was kind of a weird, like, how did I feel about this?\n\n01:20:07.500 --> 01:20:08.500\nThey were remaking this movie.\n\n01:20:08.500 --> 01:20:13.500\nI was meeting all these people, but I remembered having made a couple of movies that were traumatic,\n\n01:20:13.500 --> 01:20:17.500\nlike that they were all probably in shock and that had been a very difficult experience.\n\n01:20:17.500 --> 01:20:18.500\nAnd it really had been.\n\n01:20:18.500 --> 01:20:22.500\nAnd so I decided to just interview them about that.\n\n01:20:22.500 --> 01:20:24.500\nAnd I interviewed everyone I could.\n\n01:20:24.500 --> 01:20:27.500\nI interviewed the writer that we got credit from.\n\n01:20:27.500 --> 01:20:28.500\nI interviewed the president.\n\n01:20:28.500 --> 01:20:29.500\nI interviewed the director.\n\n01:20:29.500 --> 01:20:31.500\nAnd I would just sit there and say, well, what was that like?\n\n01:20:31.500 --> 01:20:33.500\nAnd how did that happen?\n\n01:20:33.500 --> 01:20:36.500\nAnd they sort of remembered that somehow.\n\n01:20:36.500 --> 01:20:38.500\nAnd when the movie came out, it didn't do that well.\n\n01:20:38.500 --> 01:20:41.500\nI got a call from the president of production saying, why don't you come in here and tell\n\n01:20:41.500 --> 01:20:43.500\nus any Robocop ideas you have?\n\n01:20:43.500 --> 01:20:48.500\nAnd I went in and I said, well, you know, there was, I started telling him this idea I had.\n\n01:20:48.500 --> 01:20:53.500\nAnd he said, are you pitching me the original sequel that you guys wrote back in 1988?\n\n01:20:53.500 --> 01:20:55.500\nAnd I said, well, yeah, kind of.\n\n01:20:55.500 --> 01:20:57.500\nAnd he said, oh, okay.\n\n01:20:57.500 --> 01:21:00.500\nAnd that sort of has set us off in a different direction.\n\n01:21:00.500 --> 01:21:02.500\nOh, fuck yeah.\n\n01:21:02.500 --> 01:21:04.500\nBaby.\n\n01:21:04.500 --> 01:21:05.500\nAre you kidding me?\n\n01:21:05.500 --> 01:21:06.500\nNo, but we'll see.\n\n01:21:06.500 --> 01:21:08.500\nThere's a lot of work to be done.\n\n01:21:08.500 --> 01:21:11.500\nAnd then Neil Blumkamp came swooping in when he heard they were going to do it.\n\n01:21:11.500 --> 01:21:13.500\nAnd look at Rob.\n\n01:21:13.500 --> 01:21:15.500\nHe was going to do it for a while.\n\n01:21:15.500 --> 01:21:20.500\nHe said, well, there's one funny story about it.\n\n01:21:20.500 --> 01:21:22.500\nThen it didn't work out.\n\n01:21:22.500 --> 01:21:26.500\nThey developed a few scripts and he had a bunch of different ideas.\n\n01:21:26.500 --> 01:21:28.500\nAnd I don't think it ever really came together.\n\n01:21:28.500 --> 01:21:31.500\nBut at one point he decided, and I thought this was interesting.\n\n01:21:31.500 --> 01:21:35.500\nHe said, we really got to go and do it like it happened right after the first one.\n\n01:21:35.500 --> 01:21:37.500\nThat it was Verhoeven's next movie.\n\n01:21:37.500 --> 01:21:40.500\nHe said, I'm going to do it just like Paul Verhoeven.\n\n01:21:40.500 --> 01:21:43.500\nSo the other day I'm sitting with Paul Verhoeven.\n\n01:21:43.500 --> 01:21:47.500\nHe said, yeah, he said he was going to do it just like Paul Verhoeven.\n\n01:21:47.500 --> 01:21:49.500\nI can't quite do Paul's voice.\n\n01:21:49.500 --> 01:21:50.500\nIt sounds better.\n\n01:21:50.500 --> 01:21:53.500\nAnd he said, but he said, I can't do it like Paul Verhoeven.\n\n01:21:53.500 --> 01:21:57.500\nHe said, because I won't have the same set of circumstances creatively.\n\n01:21:57.500 --> 01:22:00.500\nI'm not trying to make a movie for $10 million.\n\n01:22:00.500 --> 01:22:02.500\nI don't have John Davidson.\n\n01:22:02.500 --> 01:22:03.500\nI don't have Phil Tippett then.\n\n01:22:03.500 --> 01:22:04.500\nI don't have you.\n\n01:22:04.500 --> 01:22:06.500\nI don't have all these people together.\n\n01:22:06.500 --> 01:22:11.500\nAnd for him, that's as much a part of the creative thing in that moment as anything else.\n\n01:22:11.500 --> 01:22:16.500\nYeah, because that movie does kind of feel like...\n\n01:22:16.500 --> 01:22:21.500\nAnd Die Hard 2, that's more of a kind of a larger production, maybe.\n\n01:22:21.500 --> 01:22:24.500\nBut they feel like B-movies that were done perfectly.\n\n01:22:24.500 --> 01:22:28.500\nAnd they kind of feel like they were made in secrets.\n\n01:22:28.500 --> 01:22:30.500\nThey were made for you.\n\n01:22:30.500 --> 01:22:35.500\nWhen you walk into the theater, we turned over a rock and found a diamond.\n\n01:22:35.500 --> 01:22:39.500\nIt's not like you go in there and there's this giant tent pole kind of thing.\n\n01:22:39.500 --> 01:22:41.500\nWell, they're not shoving it down your throat as we were talking.\n\n01:22:41.500 --> 01:22:42.500\nYeah, exactly.\n\n01:22:42.500 --> 01:22:43.500\nIt's like the Robocop.\n\n01:22:43.500 --> 01:22:48.500\nI feel a personal relationship with that in a way that I don't feel with like E.T.\n\n01:22:48.500 --> 01:22:52.500\nor things like that that are just these giant juggernaut kind of things.\n\n01:22:52.500 --> 01:22:56.500\nI think that might have something to do with just not to sound like an old cane shaker,\n\n01:22:56.500 --> 01:23:01.500\nbut I think it just has to do with the singularity that hasn't happened yet, which is CG.\n\n01:23:01.500 --> 01:23:08.500\nWhen CG starts to happen, the vastness of your world is not related in any way to your budget.\n\n01:23:08.500 --> 01:23:14.500\nIf Kronenberg wants to reboot the fly, he has to rent a warehouse.\n\n01:23:14.500 --> 01:23:16.500\nHe has to build telepods.\n\n01:23:16.500 --> 01:23:21.500\nAnd these characters, these Rick Bakers, these Phil Tippets, these craftsmen have to come in\n\n01:23:21.500 --> 01:23:26.500\nand figure out how to make a beetle into a person and vice versa.\n\n01:23:26.500 --> 01:23:34.500\nAnd there's a relationship there between budget, scope, but more importantly, like,\n\n01:23:34.500 --> 01:23:38.500\noh, if this guy is going to become a fly in this movie, then it's all the more important\n\n01:23:38.500 --> 01:23:42.500\nthat we understand that he's a human being because of the budget,\n\n01:23:42.500 --> 01:23:46.500\nbecause of the practicality of the makeup and everything.\n\n01:23:46.500 --> 01:23:50.500\nWe can't waste anyone's time here on an emotional level.\n\n01:23:50.500 --> 01:23:54.500\nAnd then you start to get into like, okay, you're going to show up at Warner Brothers.\n\n01:23:54.500 --> 01:23:57.500\nThere's going to be a 90-foot sheet of green.\n\n01:23:57.500 --> 01:24:01.500\nYou're not going to be in a scene with any other actor.\n\n01:24:01.500 --> 01:24:03.500\nWe just need your head.\n\n01:24:03.500 --> 01:24:05.500\nWe're going to scan it from 360 degrees.\n\n01:24:05.500 --> 01:24:10.500\nSign this form that says, if you die, you can be a cracker.\n\n0