 sin,\n\n01:25:27.500 --> 01:25:30.500\nthat they were going to be casting this actor with no,\n\n01:25:30.500 --> 01:25:34.500\nthis character was going to have no eyes, no nose, no ears.\n\n01:25:34.500 --> 01:25:36.500\nAnd it was so important.\n\n01:25:36.500 --> 01:25:40.500\nIt was a picture like these auditions where these actors are coming in and standing under a sheet\n\n01:25:40.500 --> 01:25:46.500\nthat's on C stands and the only thing visible is their lips and that Peter Weller walked away with the part.\n\n01:25:46.500 --> 01:25:47.500\nNot the case at all.\n\n01:25:47.500 --> 01:25:49.500\nHe was Bucca Rubanzi.\n\n01:25:49.500 --> 01:25:52.500\nWell, it really helps that Peter was really thin.\n\n01:25:52.500 --> 01:25:54.500\nThat helps a lot when you're building a suit like that.\n\n01:25:54.500 --> 01:25:58.500\nAnd so if you put the wrong person in the suit, you're going to get the Michelin man.\n\n01:25:58.500 --> 01:26:03.500\nBut he's very, he also has this kind of perfect look of,\n\n01:26:03.500 --> 01:26:06.500\nI used to say when I was being meaner,\n\n01:26:06.500 --> 01:26:11.500\nbut he has this kind of tragic look, mythic self pity or something.\n\n01:26:11.500 --> 01:26:15.500\nBut there's a tragedy about his face that really works well in that.\n\n01:26:15.500 --> 01:26:17.500\nBut no, he's got those kissy lips.\n\n01:26:17.500 --> 01:26:22.500\nWe had, we always, I always thought you needed a real actor in the park.\n\n01:26:22.500 --> 01:26:25.500\nWe had, we went out to a bunch of different people came in.\n\n01:26:25.500 --> 01:26:27.500\nI mean, Keith Carradine wanted to do it.\n\n01:26:27.500 --> 01:26:32.500\nRobert Carradine, no, not David Carradine really wanted to do it.\n\n01:26:32.500 --> 01:26:36.500\nAnd so we had all those kinds of things, but it came down to, I think...\n\n01:26:36.500 --> 01:26:39.500\nThere's a great SNL sketch here, obviously.\n\n01:26:39.500 --> 01:26:42.500\nJack Lemon and the Robocop.\n\n01:26:42