03.500\nso much to do with location\n\n01:43:03.500 --> 01:43:05.500\nscouting, choreography.\n\n01:43:05.500 --> 01:43:07.500\nIt's the fact that Robocop\n\n01:43:07.500 --> 01:43:09.500\nafter fleeing at 209\n\n01:43:09.500 --> 01:43:11.500\nand he goes out front and now\n\n01:43:11.500 --> 01:43:13.500\nthe floodlights come on him\n\n01:43:13.500 --> 01:43:15.500\nand his own brother policemen\n\n01:43:15.500 --> 01:43:17.500\nhave been assigned to kill him.\n\n01:43:17.500 --> 01:43:19.500\nThey open fire on him.\n\n01:43:19.500 --> 01:43:21.500\nHe retreats into the parking garage\n\n01:43:21.500 --> 01:43:23.500\njust a way, but it's like\n\n01:43:23.500 --> 01:43:25.500\nI don't know if Piric Victory is the right description\n\n01:43:25.500 --> 01:43:27.500\nof it, but he\n\n01:43:27.500 --> 01:43:29.500\nhe's in a parking\n\n01:43:29.500 --> 01:43:31.500\ngarage laying down and he simply\n\n01:43:31.500 --> 01:43:33.500\nrolls\n\n01:43:33.500 --> 01:43:35.500\nlike\n\n01:43:35.500 --> 01:43:37.500\nthe other day I'm having lunch with Paul Verhoeven\n\n01:43:37.500 --> 01:43:39.500\nand I said, so how do you work with\n\n01:43:39.500 --> 01:43:41.500\nYandaban versus how do you work with Yosef\n\n01:43:41.500 --> 01:43:43.500\nKhanna? These are the two cinematographers\n\n01:43:43.500 --> 01:43:45.500\nthat he worked with. Yandaban, by the way, showed\n\n01:43:45.500 --> 01:43:47.500\nthat I heard.\n\n01:43:47.500 --> 01:43:49.500\nHe told me this one was this way\n\n01:43:49.500 --> 01:43:51.500\nand this one was that way and he said\n\n01:43:51.500 --> 01:43:53.500\nYost always had really good ideas\n\n01:43:53.500 --> 01:43:55.500\nand I remember this and he told me this\n\n01:43:55.500 --> 01:43:57.500\nI remember Yosef going, oh wait, over here\n\n01:43:57.500 --> 01:43:59.500\nsee where all these ramps are going? He can get away\n\n01:43:59.500 --> 01:44:01.500\nthat way. And no human could?\n\n01:44:01.500 --> 01:44:03.500\nI don't know, it just worked out.\n\n01:44:03.500 --> 01:44:05.500\nIt's things that works in movies. I mean he's surrounded with Kevlar.\n\n01:44:05.500 --> 01:44:07.500\nIt's his blessing in his curse.\n\n01:44:07.500 --> 01:44:09.500\nPaul just said\n\n01:44:09.500 --> 01:44:11.500\nit was so lovely he had that idea because\n\n01:44:11.500 --> 01:44:13.500\nit got us out of this problem.\n\n01:44:13.500 --> 01:44:15.500\nJust think that there's\n\n01:44:15.500 --> 01:44:17.500\nno way, sometimes in my worst moments\n\n01:44:17.500 --> 01:44:19.500\nI'm rehearsing myself because I'm like\n\n01:44:19.500 --> 01:44:21.500\nI imagine you writing that somehow.\n\n01:44:21.500 --> 01:44:23.500\nI didn't write that.\n\n01:44:23.500 --> 01:44:25.500\nIn the script, how did he get out of there?\n\n01:44:25.500 --> 01:44:27.500\nI think there was a cut and then a new scene\n\n01:44:27.500 --> 01:44:29.500\nand he was running away and there was nobody around.\n\n01:44:29.500 --> 01:44:31.500\nSomething like that.\n\n01:44:31.500 --> 01:44:33.500\nYou did like a newspaper\n\n01:44:33.500 --> 01:44:35.500\nand Robocampus came out.\n\n01:44:35.500 --> 01:44:37.500\nIt was heroin.\n\n01:44:37.500 --> 01:44:39.500\nHe had to be saved by Lewis.\n\n01:44:39.500 --> 01:44:41.500\nExtreme, extreme.\n\n01:44:41.500 --> 01:44:43.500\nRobot man gets away.\n\n01:44:43.500 --> 01:44:45.500\nMust have cost him a fortune.\n\n01:44:45.500 --> 01:44:47.500\nAnd says,\n\n01:44:47.500 --> 01:44:49.500\nMurphy is me, Lewis.\n\n01:44:49.500 --> 01:44:51.500\nWe knew that.\n\n01:44:51.500 --> 01:44:53.500\nIn fact, I once pitched that to Stan Lee.\n\n01:44:53.500 --> 01:44:55.500\nStan Lee liked that so much.\n\n01:44:55.500 --> 01:44:57.500\nHe said, oh wait, here's the really good part\n\n01:44:57.500 --> 01:44:59.500\nwhere he comes and finds his character.\n\n01:44:59.500 --> 01:45:01.500\nWhat you don't know is that\n\n01:45:01.500 --> 01:45:03.500\nthis almost was a Marvel comic book.\n\n01:45:03.500 --> 01:45:05.500\nAnd thank God it wasn't because they were going to buy it.\n\n01:45:05.500 --> 01:45:07.500\nStan Lee wanted to buy it\n\n01:45:07.500 --> 01:45:09.500\nat a certain point for a comic book.\n\n01:45:09.500 --> 01:45:11.500\nThen he asked me if it was\n\n01:45:11.500 --> 01:45:13.500\nhadn't I just read Deathlock\n\n01:45:13.500 --> 01:45:15.500\nand they don't know it anyway.\n\n01:45:15.500 --> 01:45:17.500\nAnd then they decided, because Marvel wasn't a very successful company,\n\n01:45:17.500 --> 01:45:19.500\nthen they decided not to do it.\n\n01:45:19.500 --> 01:45:21.500\nAnd it went to Orion.\n\n01:45:21.500 --> 01:45:23.500\nThank God for Stan Lee's lack of success.\n\n01:45:23.500 --> 01:45:25.500\nWell, he did okay after that.\n\n01:45:25.500 --> 01:45:27.500\nThat's so funny.\n\n01:45:27.500 --> 01:45:29.500\nI love the baller and I'm going to be a cynic\n\n01:45:29.500 --> 01:45:31.500\nand say, I bet Stan Lee\n\n01:45:31.500 --> 01:45:33.500\nas a Hail Mary in every meeting\n\n01:45:33.500 --> 01:45:35.500\nback then would say,\n\n01:45:35.500 --> 01:45:37.500\nnever having even seen Deathlock,\n\n01:45:37.500 --> 01:45:39.500\nthat he would just go,\n\n01:45:39.500 --> 01:45:41.500\nare you sure this isn't just Deathlock?\n\n01:45:41.500 --> 01:45:43.500\nBecause 10% of the time a writer\n\n01:45:43.500 --> 01:45:45.500\nwould cave and go, yeah, it is.\n\n01:45:45.500 --> 01:45:47.500\nI didn't realize how dangerous it was\n\n01:45:47.500 --> 01:45:49.500\nto talk to people like that at the time.\n\n01:45:49.500 --> 01:45:51.500\nBecause they had all these characters,\n\n01:45:51.500 --> 01:45:53.500\nbut I think Marvel was more a bun.\n\n01:45:53.500 --> 01:45:55.500\nThere was a secretary\n\n01:45:55.500 --> 01:45:57.500\nand one other guy in Stan Lee out here\n\n01:45:57.500 --> 01:45:59.500\nand that was it.\n\n01:45:59.500 --> 01:46:01.500\nI met him when I was a young executive universal\n\n01:46:01.500 --> 01:46:03.500\nand he had nothing better to do\n\n01:46:03.500 --> 01:46:05.500\nthan go out to have lunch with me.\n\n01:46:05.500 --> 01:46:07.500\nWho at the\n\n01:46:07.500 --> 01:46:09.500\nFortune Cookie Place writes\n\n01:46:09.500 --> 01:46:11.500\nI don't know,\n\n01:46:11.500 --> 01:46:13.500\nbut it was right on Robertson.\n\n01:46:13.500 --> 01:46:15.500\nIt was right there.\n\n01:46:15.500 --> 01:46:17.500\nFortune Cookies were badass though.\n\n01:46:17.500 --> 01:46:19.500\nDid you save that Fortune Cookie?\n\n01:46:19.500 --> 01:46:21.500\nI don't know.\n\n01:46:21.500 --> 01:46:23.500\nI might be somewhere in a box.\n\n01:46:23.500 --> 01:46:25.500\nThey became advice cookies.\n\n01:46:25.500 --> 01:46:27.500\nThey became like, you know, sometimes wearing a tie\n\n01:46:27.500 --> 01:46:29.500\ncan make you feel more confident.\n\n01:46:29.500 --> 01:46:31.500\nDid someone start suing Fortune Cookies?\n\n01:46:31.500 --> 01:46:33.500\nBecause they used to say like,\n\n01:46:33.500 --> 01:46:35.500\na dude's going to murder you with something red.\n\n01:46:35.500 --> 01:46:37.500\nThey were fun.\n\n01:46:37.500 --> 01:46:39.500\nDuck.\n\n01:46:39.500 --> 01:46:41.500\nThat was the menu, you dummy.\n\n01:46:45.500 --> 01:46:47.500\nBiggest cookie I ever saw.\n\n01:46:47.500 --> 01:46:49.500\nCouldn't even eat it.\n\n01:46:49.500 --> 01:46:51.500\nI get drunk for how to show it.\n\n01:46:53.500 --> 01:46:55.500\nI'm never going to get over\n\n01:46:55.500 --> 01:46:57.500\nthat one of the prime directors was from a Fortune Cookie.\n\n01:46:57.500 --> 01:46:59.500\nThat's just like the universe\n\n01:46:59.500 --> 01:47:01.500\njust helping you make a movie.\n\n01:47:01.500 --> 01:47:03.500\nI think there's something worth noting,\n\n01:47:03.500 --> 01:47:05.500\nwhich is your legacy.\n\n01:47:05.500 --> 01:47:07.500\nOne of your kids\n\n01:47:07.500 --> 01:47:09.500\nis this really interesting\n\n01:47:09.500 --> 01:47:11.500\nand the description of their work\n\n01:47:11.500 --> 01:47:13.500\nis so\n\n01:47:13.500 --> 01:47:15.500\nthoroughly modern.\n\n01:47:15.500 --> 01:47:17.500\nShane is a disability rights activist.\n\n01:47:17.500 --> 01:47:19.500\nThey're a lawyer.\n\n01:47:19.500 --> 01:47:21.500\nDisability activist,\n\n01:47:21.500 --> 01:47:23.500\nbut also a whole\n\n01:47:23.500 --> 01:47:25.500\ntransgender activist.\n\n01:47:29.500 --> 01:47:31.500\nIt's as if you had a child\n\n01:47:31.500 --> 01:47:33.500\nthat became\n\n01:47:33.500 --> 01:47:35.500\na trans\n\n01:47:35.500 --> 01:47:37.500\nit's a trans thing, isn't it?\n\n01:47:37.500 --> 01:47:39.500\nIt's a trans human idea\n\n01:47:39.500 --> 01:47:41.500\nin a weird way.\n\n01:47:41.500 --> 01:47:43.500\nThere is something about that.\n\n01:47:43.500 --> 01:47:45.500\nSomething future future.\n\n01:47:47.500 --> 01:47:49.500\nI imagine that must make you\n\n01:47:49.500 --> 01:47:51.500\nproud.\n\n01:47:51.500 --> 01:47:53.500\nI don't want to assume\n\n01:47:53.500 --> 01:47:55.500\nme.\n\n01:47:55.500 --> 01:47:57.500\nI'm frightened of\n\n01:47:57.500 --> 01:47:59.500\nwhat they do these days.\n\n01:47:59.500 --> 01:48:01.500\nNo, I'm kidding.\n\n01:48:01.500 --> 01:48:03.500\nThey just won a big settlement\n\n01:48:03.500 --> 01:48:05.500\nagainst a place that\n\n01:48:05.500 --> 01:48:07.500\nuses electric shock on kids.\n\n01:48:09.500 --> 01:48:11.500\nAre they an autistic activist as well?\n\n01:48:11.500 --> 01:48:13.500\nYeah.\n\n01:48:13.500 --> 01:48:15.500\nAnd also about\n\n01:48:15.500 --> 01:48:17.500\nhow the mentally ill\n\n01:48:17.500 --> 01:48:19.500\nare treated.\n\n01:48:19.500 --> 01:48:21.500\nIt's not a pretty picture, of course.\n\n01:48:21.500 --> 01:48:23.500\nBut Shane does\n\n01:48:23.500 --> 01:48:25.500\nall that kind of stuff.\n\n01:48:25.500 --> 01:48:27.500\nAnd I do feel like Shane\n\n01:48:27.500 --> 01:48:29.500\nin what they're doing\n\n01:48:29.500 --> 01:48:31.500\nis saying, I don't want to be\n\n01:48:31.500 --> 01:48:33.500\na human like other humans are.\n\n01:48:33.500 --> 01:48:35.500\nI am not a human like other humans are.\n\n01:48:35.500 --> 01:48:37.500\nBut what I am\n\n01:48:37.500 --> 01:48:39.500\nis they are autistic.\n\n01:48:39.500 --> 01:48:41.500\nThey have facial anomalies.\n\n01:48:41.500 --> 01:48:43.500\nThey don't look like other people.\n\n01:48:43.500 --> 01:48:45.500\nAnd that is an interesting experience that way\n\n01:48:45.500 --> 01:48:47.500\nto be so different\n\n01:48:47.500 --> 01:48:49.500\nin the world. I think sometimes\n\n01:48:49.500 --> 01:48:51.500\nit's extremely difficult for them.\n\n01:48:51.500 --> 01:48:53.500\nBut also it gives them a certain kind of\n\n01:48:53.500 --> 01:48:55.500\npower and audacity.\n\n01:48:55.500 --> 01:48:57.500\nOne of my favorite things\n\n01:48:57.500 --> 01:48:59.500\nthat happens occasionally, Shane will call me up\n\n01:48:59.500 --> 01:49:01.500\nand say, well, I went to the airport the other day\n\n01:49:01.500 --> 01:49:03.500\nand they talked to me like I was mentally retarded.\n\n01:49:03.500 --> 01:49:05.500\nAnd I always\n\n01:49:05.500 --> 01:49:07.500\nkind of laugh when that happens.\n\n01:49:07.500 --> 01:49:09.500\nBecause I know what's coming next.\n\n01:49:09.500 --> 01:49:11.500\nShane will tell them that they're a lawyer\n\n01:49:11.500 --> 01:49:13.500\nand watch out.\n\n01:49:15.500 --> 01:49:17.500\nWhat is their relationship with your work?\n\n01:49:19.500 --> 01:49:21.500\nYou've got this kid\n\n01:49:21.500 --> 01:49:23.500\nand you're going through\n\n01:49:23.500 --> 01:49:25.500\ndecades of a screenwriting career\n\n01:49:25.500 --> 01:49:27.500\nand you're\n\n01:49:27.500 --> 01:49:29.500\ncelebrated. You're on red carpets.\n\n01:49:29.500 --> 01:49:31.500\nThere's VHS boxes\n\n01:49:31.500 --> 01:49:33.500\nlying at the grocery store.\n\n01:49:33.500 --> 01:49:35.500\nI don't know how the ages work out.\n\n01:49:35.500 --> 01:49:37.500\nHow old Shane was and how old Casey was.\n\n01:49:37.500 --> 01:49:39.500\nShane was born the year the movie came out\n\n01:49:39.500 --> 01:49:41.500\nand my son was born\n\n01:49:41.500 --> 01:49:43.500\ntwo years later.\n\n01:49:43.500 --> 01:49:45.500\nThey grew up with that in the shadow of that.\n\n01:49:45.500 --> 01:49:47.500\nI often think\n\n01:49:47.500 --> 01:49:49.500\nthat it's almost\n\n01:49:49.500 --> 01:49:51.500\nhard to see.\n\n01:49:51.500 --> 01:49:53.500\nIt's just like everywhere around.\n\n01:49:53.500 --> 01:49:55.500\nAnd\n\n01:49:55.500 --> 01:49:57.500\nI think it was later\n\n01:49:57.500 --> 01:49:59.500\nthat they would both in different ways experience something about it.\n\n01:49:59.500 --> 01:50:01.500\nI noticed that both of them don't talk about it much.\n\n01:50:01.500 --> 01:50:03.500\nOccasionally they'll pull it out\n\n01:50:03.500 --> 01:50:05.500\nif it's the right thing to pull out.\n\n01:50:05.500 --> 01:50:07.500\nWhich I'm really happy that they can get anything out of it at all.\n\n01:50:07.500 --> 01:50:09.500\nBut mostly it's just like\n\n01:50:09.500 --> 01:50:11.500\nI think they had to put up with all the other parts of me.\n\n01:50:11.500 --> 01:50:13.500\nIs it weird for you\n\n01:50:13.500 --> 01:50:15.500\nwhen you hear\n\n01:50:15.500 --> 01:50:17.500\nDan and Rob and I\n\n01:50:17.500 --> 01:50:19.500\nprobably half the people you've met\n\n01:50:19.500 --> 01:50:21.500\nsince 1987\n\n01:50:21.500 --> 01:50:23.500\ntalk about the stuff that you've made\n\n01:50:23.500 --> 01:50:25.500\nand kind of\n\n01:50:25.500 --> 01:50:27.500\nwhen they talk about what it meant to them\n\n01:50:27.500 --> 01:50:29.500\nor what their reaction to it is\n\n01:50:29.500 --> 01:50:31.500\ndo you ever just feel like\n\n01:50:31.500 --> 01:50:33.500\nthey're\n\n01:50:33.500 --> 01:50:35.500\nyou're hearing them say things\n\n01:50:35.500 --> 01:50:37.500\nabout the movie that you didn't intend\n\n01:50:37.500 --> 01:50:39.500\nbut like\n\n01:50:39.500 --> 01:50:41.500\nI actually don't think it has that much to\n\n01:50:41.500 --> 01:50:43.500\nall of that is it's a wonderful thing that happens\n\n01:50:43.500 --> 01:50:45.500\nand I kind of like it\n\n01:50:45.500 --> 01:50:47.500\nbut it doesn't have anything to do with me.\n\n01:50:47.500 --> 01:50:49.500\nIt's not me, it's the movie\n\n01:50:49.500 --> 01:50:51.500\nand the fact that people like it\n\n01:50:51.500 --> 01:50:53.500\nand are in any way inspired by it\n\n01:50:53.500 --> 01:50:55.500\nis sort of amazing to me\n\n01:50:55.500 --> 01:50:57.500\nand it wasn't something I thought\n\n01:50:57.500 --> 01:50:59.500\ncould ever happen.\n\n01:50:59.500 --> 01:51:01.500\nI've heard people say well the reason I went\n\n01:51:01.500 --> 01:51:03.500\nto film school sitting literally\n\n01:51:03.500 --> 01:51:05.500\nwhere I was sitting at UCLA is because of this movie\n\n01:51:05.500 --> 01:51:07.500\nand that's weird.\n\n01:51:07.500 --> 01:51:09.500\nSometimes I think well I hope that was weird.\n\n01:51:09.500 --> 01:51:11.500\nWhen it was done\n\n01:51:11.500 --> 01:51:13.500\nwhen the script was done went into production\n\n01:51:13.500 --> 01:51:15.500\nand they're making the film and you got through the suit\n\n01:51:15.500 --> 01:51:17.500\nproblems and all the stuff and you were going into\n\n01:51:17.500 --> 01:51:19.500\nediting how confident were you\n\n01:51:19.500 --> 01:51:21.500\nthat this was going to be a success or a failure\n\n01:51:21.500 --> 01:51:23.500\nor was it totally up like it?\n\n01:51:23.500 --> 01:51:25.500\nI remember the first time we saw the first cut of it\n\n01:51:25.500 --> 01:51:27.500\nit was really and I had never seen a first cut\n\n01:51:27.500 --> 01:51:29.500\nof anything before and I remember the\n\n01:51:29.500 --> 01:51:31.500\ndirector and I walked out like\n\n01:51:31.500 --> 01:51:33.500\nwhat is that and the sound\n\n01:51:33.500 --> 01:51:35.500\nwas all wrong and everything was wrong and when\n\n01:51:35.500 --> 01:51:37.500\nhe walked it sound like he was walking on toilet\n\n01:51:37.500 --> 01:51:39.500\nplungers it was just terrible.\n\n01:51:39.500 --> 01:51:41.500\nBig shake like that.\n\n01:51:41.500 --> 01:51:43.500\nIt was like that and then\n\n01:51:43.500 --> 01:51:45.500\nall the stuff it was great\n\n01:51:45.500 --> 01:51:47.500\nlearning process for me and then all the sound came in\n\n01:51:47.500 --> 01:51:49.500\nand Steve Flick who did all those\n\n01:51:49.500 --> 01:51:51.500\nsounds and did the roar and put the\n\n01:51:51.500 --> 01:51:53.500\nlion's roar.\n\n01:51:53.500 --> 01:51:55.500\nThe footsteps. Could you talk about the footsteps\n\n01:51:55.500 --> 01:51:57.500\nor what kind of footsteps?\n\n01:51:57.500 --> 01:51:59.500\nThat's because Steve Flick is a genius\n\n01:51:59.500 --> 01:52:01.500\nand Steve Flick did\n\n01:52:01.500 --> 01:52:03.500\nPulp Fiction and he did Starship and he was\n\n01:52:03.500 --> 01:52:05.500\njust the genius sound guy.\n\n01:52:05.500 --> 01:52:07.500\nDid he ever say like oh that's a hot dog\n\n01:52:07.500 --> 01:52:09.500\nvendor?\n\n01:52:09.500 --> 01:52:11.500\nYou know Steve was the first guy who was saying\n\n01:52:11.500 --> 01:52:13.500\nwell there's 100 tracks\n\n01:52:13.500 --> 01:52:15.500\nand you know\n\n01:52:15.500 --> 01:52:17.500\nso try to figure out what that is.\n\n01:52:17.500 --> 01:52:19.500\nSometimes you get those fun things though\n\n01:52:19.500 --> 01:52:21.500\nlike the exorcist with the cage\n\n01:52:21.500 --> 01:52:23.500\nof bees or someone else.\n\n01:52:23.500 --> 01:52:25.500\nThere's a lion roar and an ape roar\n\n01:52:25.500 --> 01:52:27.500\nin that thing that you're doing with\n\n01:52:27.500 --> 01:52:29.500\nEd 209. That's really a lion\n\n01:52:29.500 --> 01:52:31.500\nand an ape and something else.\n\n01:52:31.500 --> 01:52:33.500\nI honestly just thought that was the MGM lion.\n\n01:52:33.500 --> 01:52:35.500\nNo it was an MGM until later.\n\n01:52:35.500 --> 01:52:37.500\nThat's a good idea we should put that in.\n\n01:52:37.500 --> 01:52:39.500\nI'll tell them.\n\n01:52:39.500 --> 01:52:41.500\nBut anyway to answer your question\n\n01:52:41.500 --> 01:52:43.500\nit was like\n\n01:52:43.500 --> 01:52:45.500\nI didn't know if it would work. I remember\n\n01:52:45.500 --> 01:52:47.500\nhoping it would work.\n\n01:52:47.500 --> 01:52:49.500\nAnd then I saw it and I thought\n\n01:52:49.500 --> 01:52:51.500\nI had to see it in front of an audience for the first time\n\n01:52:51.500 --> 01:52:53.500\nand people laughed right away and I thought\n\n01:52:53.500 --> 01:52:55.500\noh that's good. And then the second screening\n\n01:52:55.500 --> 01:52:57.500\nthey laughed in all the same places.\n\n01:52:57.500 --> 01:52:59.500\nOne of the things that happened in the first screening was\n\n01:52:59.500 --> 01:53:01.500\nwhen Murphy gets killed\n\n01:53:01.500 --> 01:53:03.500\nin the first version it was much bloodier\n\n01:53:03.500 --> 01:53:05.500\nand there were these shots of the floor\n\n01:53:05.500 --> 01:53:07.500\nthat were covered with blood.\n\n01:53:07.500 --> 01:53:09.500\nEvery time that happened\n\n01:53:09.500 --> 01:53:11.500\nwomen would get up and leave the room\n\n01:53:11.500 --> 01:53:13.500\nand when we cut the floor out\n\n01:53:13.500 --> 01:53:15.500\nand we cut shots to a blood out\n\n01:53:15.500 --> 01:53:17.500\nit\n\n01:53:17.500 --> 01:53:19.500\nthen only one person got it.\n\n01:53:19.500 --> 01:53:21.500\nI was tired. It's a traumatic thing\n\n01:53:21.500 --> 01:53:23.500\nand I guess that's a tight rub\n\n01:53:23.500 --> 01:53:25.500\nbecause it's your point of immersion\n\n01:53:25.500 --> 01:53:27.500\nbut I guess if you're overdoing it\n\n01:53:27.500 --> 01:53:29.500\nand it feels pornographic then the women are going to go\n\n01:53:29.500 --> 01:53:31.500\nyou know it seems like you're having fun with this\n\n01:53:31.500 --> 01:53:33.500\nas opposed to it seems like maybe you\n\n01:53:33.500 --> 01:53:35.500\nunderstand.\n\n01:53:35.500 --> 01:53:37.500\nNow it occurs to me that there's a lot of stuffing\n\n01:53:37.500 --> 01:53:39.500\ncoming out of\n\n01:53:39.500 --> 01:53:41.500\nit's almost like it's a horrible violent killing\n\n01:53:41.500 --> 01:53:43.500\nof a teddy bear.\n\n01:53:43.500 --> 01:53:45.500\nWell if you look at it it's also a crucifixion\n\n01:53:45.500 --> 01:53:47.500\nhe plays it that way for a second.\n\n01:53:47.500 --> 01:53:49.500\nWell he gets his hands shot off. It's so awful.\n\n01:53:49.500 --> 01:53:51.500\nThere's even a moment where he's like\n\n01:53:51.500 --> 01:53:53.500\nlike that and that was one of the things\n\n01:53:53.500 --> 01:53:55.500\nso to ask you to answer a question\n\n01:53:55.500 --> 01:53:57.500\nearlier Verhoeven coming into it\n\n01:53:57.500 --> 01:53:59.500\nVerhoeven reads the second draft\n\n01:53:59.500 --> 01:54:01.500\nand reads the title page Robocop\n\n01:54:01.500 --> 01:54:03.500\nThe Future of Law Enforcement and he goes\n\n01:54:03.500 --> 01:54:05.500\nI'm never going to do this and he doesn't read the script\n\n01:54:05.500 --> 01:54:07.500\nand so\n\n01:54:07.500 --> 01:54:09.500\nBarbara Boyle at Orion Pictures\n\n01:54:09.500 --> 01:54:11.500\nsent it to him and said why don't you read it\n\n01:54:11.500 --> 01:54:13.500\nmaybe you could read it again\n\n01:54:13.500 --> 01:54:15.500\nfor the subtext so he gave it to his wife\n\n01:54:15.500 --> 01:54:17.500\nMartine\n\n01:54:17.500 --> 01:54:19.500\nand she read it and she said you know\n\n01:54:19.500 --> 01:54:21.500\nI think you should read this I think there's going to be\n\n01:54:21.500 --> 01:54:23.500\nsomething in it that you like\n\n01:54:23.500 --> 01:54:25.500\nand he got to the scene with the hand being blown off\n\n01:54:25.500 --> 01:54:27.500\nand he says he said\n\n01:54:27.500 --> 01:54:29.500\nlet's go we're going to go to America we're going to go do this\n\n01:54:29.500 --> 01:54:31.500\nso he really said he'd never seen anything like that\n\n01:54:31.500 --> 01:54:33.500\nhe liked that he responded well to that\n\n01:54:33.500 --> 01:54:35.500\ncan you say there was a lot of like\n\n01:54:35.500 --> 01:54:37.500\nJesus metaphors\n\n01:54:37.500 --> 01:54:39.500\nin there like he's walking on the water\n\n01:54:39.500 --> 01:54:41.500\nwe always knew we were playing around\n\n01:54:41.500 --> 01:54:43.500\nwith Jesus and Frankenstein\n\n01:54:43.500 --> 01:54:45.500\ndepending on which\n\n01:54:45.500 --> 01:54:47.500\nand he's very interested in Jesus\n\n01:54:47.500 --> 01:54:49.500\nhe actually was a Jesus scholar\n\n01:54:49.500 --> 01:54:51.500\nfor 25 years and he really wanted to do\n\n01:54:51.500 --> 01:54:53.500\nthe story of Jesus but when we were in Pittsburgh\n\n01:54:53.500 --> 01:54:55.500\nand we were in that\n\n01:54:55.500 --> 01:54:57.500\nthat steel plant\n\n01:54:57.500 --> 01:54:59.500\nand he took me over\n\n01:54:59.500 --> 01:55:01.500\nto that tank and he said that with these big\n\n01:55:01.500 --> 01:55:03.500\nwalls and he said that's one of the most beautiful\n\n01:55:03.500 --> 01:55:05.500\nthings I've ever seen and it's like\n\n01:55:05.500 --> 01:55:07.500\nthe walls of an ancient city and\n\n01:55:07.500 --> 01:55:09.500\nI said well that's great we got to use that\n\n01:55:09.500 --> 01:55:11.500\nand so that became the walking on the water\n\n01:55:11.500 --> 01:55:13.500\nscene came out of that did Martine and he\n\n01:55:13.500 --> 01:55:15.500\nbreak up before showgirls\n\n01:55:15.500 --> 01:55:17.500\nno okay sorry\n\n01:55:17.500 --> 01:55:19.500\nno no no\n\n01:55:19.500 --> 01:55:21.500\nthey're still happily married\n\n01:55:21.500 --> 01:55:23.500\ntogether all these many years later\n\n01:55:23.500 --> 01:55:25.500\nalright why\n\n01:55:25.500 --> 01:55:27.500\ndid you like showgirls\n\n01:55:27.500 --> 01:55:29.500\nwell you know\n\n01:55:29.500 --> 01:55:31.500\nshowgirls was the movie he was doing\n\n01:55:31.500 --> 01:55:33.500\nwhen\n\n01:55:33.500 --> 01:55:35.500\nwe were trying to get him to do it\n\n01:55:35.500 --> 01:55:37.500\nwhen I wanted him to do structure\n\n01:55:37.500 --> 01:55:39.500\ntalking about the things that make you feel good\n\n01:55:39.500 --> 01:55:41.500\nwell there's that guy, there's my partner\n\n01:55:41.500 --> 01:55:43.500\nthere's the other piston of this engine\n\n01:55:43.500 --> 01:55:45.500\nbut minus me\n\n01:55:45.500 --> 01:55:47.500\nyeah there was a moment where Paul was going to be\n\n01:55:47.500 --> 01:55:49.500\nno Paul had already done two movies in a row\n\n01:55:49.500 --> 01:55:51.500\nthat Paul was the biggest director\n\n01:55:51.500 --> 01:55:53.500\nin Hollywood for a moment and a half there\n\n01:55:53.500 --> 01:55:55.500\nbecause he'd done total recall\n\n01:55:55.500 --> 01:55:57.500\nhe's amazing\n\n01:55:57.500 --> 01:55:59.500\nhe clearly is\n\n01:55:59.500 --> 01:56:01.500\nand then he did showgirls\n\n01:56:01.500 --> 01:56:03.500\nthere was almost a moment where I thought\n\n01:56:03.500 --> 01:56:05.500\nhe won't do this movie because he can do anything\n\n01:56:05.500 --> 01:56:07.500\nand so when showgirls\n\n01:56:07.500 --> 01:56:09.500\ncrashed and burned a little it was kind of good for me\n\n01:56:09.500 --> 01:56:11.500\nand actually\n\n01:56:11.500 --> 01:56:13.500\nthe sort of neat thing about him was\n\n01:56:13.500 --> 01:56:15.500\nI went over to see him like on a Thursday\n\n01:56:15.500 --> 01:56:17.500\nthe movie was going to come out on a Friday\n\n01:56:17.500 --> 01:56:19.500\nand he was so full of himself\n\n01:56:19.500 --> 01:56:21.500\nand he was so like yeah maybe we'll do your movie\n\n01:56:21.500 --> 01:56:23.500\nI'm not sure\n\n01:56:23.500 --> 01:56:25.500\nwe'll buy Mars or something like that\n\n01:56:25.500 --> 01:56:27.500\nand then it came out\n\n01:56:27.500 --> 01:56:29.500\nand it got bad reviews and on\n\n01:56:29.500 --> 01:56:31.500\nSunday\n\n01:56:31.500 --> 01:56:33.500\nhe came out to my house in Eagle Rock\n\n01:56:33.500 --> 01:56:35.500\nand we sat down and we started working on Starship\n\n01:56:35.500 --> 01:56:37.500\nand later on I asked him how did you recover\n\n01:56:37.500 --> 01:56:39.500\nfrom that that was such a drubbing\n\n01:56:39.500 --> 01:56:41.500\nI mean how do you deal with that because it's hard\n\n01:56:41.500 --> 01:56:43.500\nto deal with that stuff and he said I just went to work right away\n\n01:56:43.500 --> 01:56:45.500\nright with you\n\n01:56:45.500 --> 01:56:47.500\nwith me which I take\n\n01:56:47.500 --> 01:56:49.500\nit's true\n\n01:56:49.500 --> 01:56:51.500\nare you still friends with him today?\n\n01:56:51.500 --> 01:56:53.500\nI just had lunch with him on Friday\n\n01:56:53.500 --> 01:56:55.500\nlet's bring him out\n\n01:56:55.500 --> 01:56:57.500\nI told him I was going to do this\n\n01:56:57.500 --> 01:56:59.500\nand he's going to listen and now he's never\n\n01:56:59.500 --> 01:57:01.500\nwell I don't know if he'll listen\n\n01:57:01.500 --> 01:57:03.500\nwe're ending the show anyway it doesn't matter\n\n01:57:03.500 --> 01:57:05.500\nhe might hear about it maybe he won't\n\n01:57:05.500 --> 01:57:07.500\nalright thanks for coming in that's been our time everybody\n\n01:57:07.500 --> 01:57:09.500\ngive it up for Ed Neumeyer everybody\n\n01:57:09.500 --> 01:57:11.500\nthank you\n\n01:57:13.500 --> 01:57:15.500\nRob Trob\n\n01:57:17.500 --> 01:57:19.500\neverybody here at Donnie's\n\n01:57:19.500 --> 01:57:21.500\nthanks for coming Jeff Davis your mayor\n\n01:57:21.500 --> 01:57:23.500\nDan Harmon\n\n01:57:25.500 --> 01:57:27.500\nthank you all\n\n01:57:27.500 --> 01:57:29.500\nlet's all go home and watch Robocop again\n\n01:57:29.500 --> 01:57:31.500\ndrive fast and take chances\n\n01:57:31.500 --> 01:57:51.500\nbefore you get beat up\n\n01:57:51.500 --> 01:57:53.500\ndid you get any of that?\n\n01:57:53.500 --> 01:58:03.500\nit's a good show\n","cpu_time":["0.003s"],"str_size":[181949]}